 alignment correction and velocity correction) to access\nactual counter performances such as efficiency and time resolution. An\nefficiency of 97% and time resolution of 48ps are obtained. All these results\nshow that the real-size prototype is fully capable of the requirement of the\nCBM-TOF, and new designs such as self-sealing are modified into the strip\ncounter prototype to obtain even better performance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 May 2016 00:48:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-24"}
